      <title>Fresh crisis in eastern DRC</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/christianaidpodcasts/~3/pE9RSDgEWD4/828156-fresh-crisis-in-eastern-drc</link>
      <itunes:author>allypcarnwath</itunes:author>
      <itunes:duration>291</itunes:duration>
      <itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
      <itunes:keywords>Africa, aid, conflict, development, DRC, refugee</itunes:keywords>
      <description>In April, eastern DRC was plunged into fresh chaos when factions of the Congolese army mutinied, reigniting fighting in the area. The conflict has displaced thousands of ordinary Congolese people and many civilians have lost their lives. Salome Ntububa, Christian Aid's regional emergency manager for central Africa, describes the situation. </description>
