    <item>
      <title>East Africa food crisis appeal: Update</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/christianaidpodcasts/~3/JMCoP5PEWPs/591698-east-africa-food-crisis-appeal-update</link>
      <itunes:author>RossHemingway</itunes:author>
      <itunes:image href="http://cdn.avanti247.com/cdn.static0.audioboo.fm/files/images/0193/6620/6006864_intranet.jpg" />
      <itunes:duration>398</itunes:duration>
      <itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
      <itunes:keywords>Christian Aid, drought, east Africa, Kenya, malnutrition, solidarity, water, food crisis appeal, livelihoods</itunes:keywords>
      <description>Drought combined with rising food prices has left the east and the horn of Africa, especially Kenya and Ethiopia, facing a food crisis.

In August 2011, Christian Aid’s Branwen Niclas travelled to Kenya to find out how Christian Aid’s partner Christian Community Services (CCS) is helping communities face some of the driest conditions in 60 years.  

In this podcast, Branwen talks to Timothy Makutu, of CCS, about the effects of the drought and what is being done to alleviate the impact on the most vulnerable.  She also reflects on her experience of meeting those most affected. 

For more information on our work in East Africa, and to donate to the appeal, visit:
http://www.christianaid.org.uk/emergencies/current/east-africa-food-crisis-appeal/index.aspx 
</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 16 Dec 2011 16:40:19 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">tag:audioboo.fm,2011-12-16:/boos/591698</guid>
      
      <dc:creator>sbuckley@christian-aid.org (Christian Aid)</dc:creator>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[
        <div class='audio_clip boowrapper' id='audio_clip_591698'>
<div class='author_image'>
<img alt="RossHemingway" class="tall " src="http://cdn.avanti247.com/cdn.static0.audioboo.fm/files/images/0169/8095/Picture_1_tiny.png" />
