    <item>
      <title>Stigma under the lens: James' story</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/christianaidpodcasts/~3/3oyPwg-uy64/566603-stigma-under-the-lens-james-story</link>
      <itunes:author>AntoinettePowell</itunes:author>
      <itunes:duration>130</itunes:duration>
      <itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit>
      <itunes:keywords>AIDS, Christian Aid, HIV, Kenya, stigma, World AIDS Day</itunes:keywords>
      <description>This World AIDS Day, Christian Aid and Magnum Photos present powerful stories of brave people around the world who are living with HIV under the shadow of stigma.

James from Kenya was sacked from his truck-driving job on the Mombasa Highway when his employer found out he was HIV positive. 

In Kenya, 1.5 million people are living with HIV. Free antiretroviral treatment has revolutionised the lives of many, but stigma and discrimination continue to hamper an effective response to the virus and can discourage people from getting tested and seeking the support they need. 

Explore all our slideshows and help us challenge HIV stigma around the world: http://www.christianaid.org.uk/hiv
</description>
